# Campy Slack Bot

A Slack bot for Journalism Production Cycle and Management, . 

## Table of Contents
Introduction
Features
Installation
Usage
Contributing
License

## Introduction
In this project, I have implemented a Slack Bot that allows users to notify staff writers on pending assignments and grade their works. The Slack bot is a service on cloud that responds to the user commands on Slack. It can automate the management process for users on the Slack channels to collaborate.

## Features
Notify users of incomplete assignments in the team.
Grade works based on submissions.

## Installation
To use the Campy Slack Bot

Clone the repository:
`git clone https://github.com/kate-j-xia/campy-bot.git`

Navigate to the project directory:
`cd campy-bot`

Install the dependencies:
npm install

## Pre-requisites

- Join the Campy workspace and channels as necessary
- Create the necessary Google Spreadsheets, eg. Completions, etc.
- Make sure the Google sheets are filled with correct columns and values

## Usage

Use following command:
- `/campy notify` to notify users
- `/campy grade` to start grading


